  "texts": [
    "Table 1: Summary of the proposed evaluation metrics.",
    "The logits mentioned in JSC and NSDCG are from a BioBERT model pre-trained on a hierarchical ICD-10 code categories classification task.",
    "The methodology was designed to enable a fair comparison between the performance of different techniques for clinical note anonymization.",
    "A total of seven anonymization solutions were compared: two baseline techniques offered by the INCOGNI-TUS toolbox (Ribeiro et al., 2023), a fine-tuned BERT model, ClinicalBERT (Wang et al., 2023), and four prompt-based methods that leverage Microsoft's Phi-2 and Meta's Llama-3 LLMs (Gunasekar et al., 2023; Touvron et al., 2023) (including two zero-shot learning strategies and two finetuned models).",
    "The experimental dataset includes 66,645 discharge summary notes from the MIMIC III dataset (Johnson et al., 2016)."
  ],
